During his State of the Nation Address, Cyril Ramaphosa revealed his outfit is from House of Monatic, based in Cape Town. The president used this to encourage South Africans to buy local goods. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - It may have been stitched locally, but the president’s State of the Nation Address (Sona) suit wasn't all South African. During Sona, Cyril Ramaphosa revealed his outfit is from House of Monatic, based in Cape Town. The president used this to encourage South Africans to buy local goods. WATCH: No quick fixes to SA's problems: Ramaphosa The fabric used to make Ramaphosa's garments, as well as most suits in the country, is imported. Local vendors say revitalising our textile market would mean South Africa could export in a short space of time.